        "name": "LAB-3.4 CTI Event Report",
        "content": "# LAB-3.4 \u2014 Log4Shell JNDI Reference Traffic\n\n**Case:** CJ-010B  \n**Campaign:** Cinder Jackal vs ApexFin Solutions  \n**Date:** 2025-08-14  \n**ATT&CK:** T1190, T1059.004, T1105\n\n## Analyst narrative\nOptional network exploit evidence demonstrates a Log4Shell/JNDI request, LDAP reference, HTTP class retrieval, and reverse-shell style payload in a safe lab.\n\n## CTI promotion guidance\n- Promote only validated observables from TheHive/Cortex into this MISP event.\n- Keep `to_ids=false` for baseline infrastructure, documentation ranges, internal IPs, and workflow metadata.\n- Keep `to_ids=true` for behaviorally useful detection indicators such as malicious command lines, staged payload names, suspicious URLs, named pipes, and fictional campaign IOCs.\n- Add sightings during the lab when the same observable appears in Elastic/Wazuh/Zeek queries.\n\n## Source artifacts\n- pcap_log4shell_cve2021_44228_jndi_reference_2022-05-11181020.pcap\n- securityauditing_log4shell_cve2021_44228_java_serialized_object_2022-05-13045400.json\n",
